# Payment App

This is a dummy payment app consisting of two Django services/projects and a React-based frontend.

## Dependencies

- [Docker](https://www.docker.com/)

## Set Up (local)

The application is dockerized but requires some environment variables for the two Django services

##### Env variables for the Identity Service

create a `.env` file in the Identity's root directory (inside the `./identity` folder). The keys of the file are described below.

| Env key                 | Sample/Default value | Description               |
| ------------------------ | ------ | ------------------------- |
| `DATABASE_URL`          | `postgresql://docker:docker@db:5432/auth`   | This url points to the dockerized postgresSQL instance            |
| `PRIVATE_KEY`          | ``    | Base64 encoded RSA Private key   |
| `PUBLIC_KEY` | ``   | Base64 encoded RSA Public key  |



##### Env variables for the Pay Service

create a `.env` file in the Pay's root directory (inside the `./pay` folder). The keys of the file are described below.

| Env key                 | Sample/Default value | Description               |
| ------------------------ | ------ | ------------------------- |
| `DATABASE_URL`          | `postgresql://docker2:docker2@db_pay:5432/pay`   | This url points to the dockerized postgresSQL instance            |
| `PRIVATE_KEY`          | ``    | Base64 encoded RSA Private key   |
| `PUBLIC_KEY` | ``   | Base64 encoded RSA Public key  |



##### building and running application

- To build the app `docker-compose build`

- To start the app `docker-compose up`

## API Documentations
The api are documented with Swagger and can be found at the root of each Django service
- Identity docs [http://127.0.0.1:8000/](http://127.0.0.1:8000/)
- Pay docs [http://127.0.0.1:8001/](http://127.0.0.1:8001/)
